  m_Script: {fileID: 11500000, guid: 3507d679efa283143b52308c9a6a3292, type: 3}
  m_Name: GSWC_Module_1_Q2
  m_EditorClassIdentifier: Assembly-CSharp::QuestionData
  question: "You download a game to your computer. But when you open the file, the
    game doesn\u2019t start. Worse, your computer starts behaving like someone else
    is controlling it. For example, the cursor moves by itself and clicks items on
    the screen.\r\nWhat type of malware might be causing these issues?"
  answers:
  - Trojan
  - Ransomware
  - Virus
  - Worm
  maxSelections: 1
  correctAnswerIndices: 00000000
  correctMessage: The game file is probably a trojan. A trojan is a seemingly helpful
    program designed to secretly give attackers access to the device. Attackers disguise
    trojans as benign programs or files such as games. Once you run the trojan, the
    attacker can perform malicious actions such as controlling your computer remotely.
  incorrectMessage: The game file is probably a trojan. A trojan is a seemingly helpful
    program designed to secretly give attackers access to the device. Attackers disguise
    trojans as benign programs or files such as games. Once you run the trojan, the
    attacker can perform malicious actions such as controlling your computer remotely.
